import { SinglePost, SinglePostImage, SinglePostTitle, SinglePostInfo, Span, Name, SinglePostDescription, Introduction, SinglePostList, } from './Singlepost.styled' import Music from '../../image/Kpop.jpeg' import EditDelete from '../icons /EditDelete' const SinglePostMusic = () => { return ( My Favourite music Author: Dohee Lee 4 hours ago Kpop! These music has been my favourie since i was young. I remember listening to my first kpop music when i was 7 years old. It was "Into The New World" by Girls Generation, which i found extremely fascinating as i have never seen artists where they sing and dance at the same time! The music is very unique even if its similar to Western or pop music and unlike the other pop artists, the visual appeal of K-pop videos is universal. Choreography in particular can transcend cultural barriers, which is why most K-pop videos contain a signature dance move. Like the crab dance in “Gee” or the dance in "Permission to Dance" are intentionally easy to imitate.

Below is the list of current favourite artists and music!

My current favourites

  • Shut down by Blackpink
  • Typa girl by Blackpink
  • Hype boy by New Jeans
  • Butter by BTS
  • So What by STAYC
  • Illusion by Aespa
 ) } export default SinglePostMusic
